'''Life-bearers''', also known as life-witches, were [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|females]] with the rare ability to extend a male's life for five standard years after which the male would die. They existed only on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Leria Kerlsil]] and used the title "Ver" in addition to their surname. The life-bearer was sterile, thus they appeared very rarely, as genetic or [[Magic/Legends|mystical]] anomalies.

[[File:KariaVerSeryan.jpg|thumb|right|200px|[[Karia Ver Seryan]], a life-witch.]]

After the male accepted the bond by performing the [[Blood/Legends|blood]] kiss in the [[Marriage/Legends|wedding]] ceremony, the life-bearer supported him for three to five years, providing "Support," granting him the strength and vitality of a young man during this [[Time/Legends|time]]. He would also live in comfort and luxury with the life-bearer. The Support was a drain on the bearer's life energy, and she withdrew it after the three to five years, running the risk of [[Death/Legends|death]] if she did not. She then inherited all of her husband's wealth and possessions, which he typically would not have been alive to enjoy without her support in any event. Life-bearers had to recover for a [[Time/Legends|time]] after the death of a husband before they could marry again, but their gift was such that they had to provide Support for a husband or eventually grow sick and die themselves after a decade or so. They lived only by sharing the life essences of others and could not survive long without a husband to care for. Living on in this fashion, life-bearers could live several centuries.

Life-bearers disapproved of being called life-witches, seeing their ability as a blessing to help the old and the ill rather than take advantage of them.

In [[18 ABY/Legends|18 ABY]], [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] nearly married the life-bearer [[Karia Ver Seryan]] while he was searching for a bride with [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. It was only the last-second intercession of [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] that saved him from a greatly abbreviated lifespan.

==Behind the scenes==
The concept of Life-witches bears a resemblance to both [[Mind-witch]]es<ref name="TPD">"[[The Paradise Detour]]"</ref> and [[Energy Vampire|Energy vampires]].<ref name="NWO">{{CWACite|9|No Way Out}}</ref>

